{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8bec87b4-7b71-434d-98d6-24ba73c4db19","content":"Here's what to change:\n\n1. **Update NuGet packages:**\n   - Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`\n   - Update `NUnit3TestAdapter` to **5.0.0+** (it bundles Microsoft.Testing.Platform support)\n   - Add `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` or other `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.*` packages if needed\n\n2. **Add an MSBuild property** in your `.csproj` (or `Directory.Build.props`):\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n3. **Run tests** the same way:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n\n**Key notes:**\n- NUnit3TestAdapter **5.0+** is the bridge — it implements the Microsoft.Testing.Platform adapter for NUnit.\n- The `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` property tells `dotnet test` to use the new platform instead of VSTest.\n- If you use `dotnet test` CLI flags like `--filter`, the syntax stays the same, but some advanced VSTest `.runsettings` features may need adjustment.\n- You can optionally add `<GenerateEntryPoint>true</GenerateEntryPoint>` if you want a self-contained test executable (no `dotnet test` needed).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ce0389e9-aae8-412c-9abf-27fb0bbd0901","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating an NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing infrastructure, so I can answer from my knowledge without needing to explore any codebase.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about the migration steps.","outputTokens":419},"id":"0ca59d5e-96c7-4298-9527-a301618c388e","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:41:42.642Z","parentId":"e73c64a0-f1b3-408a-a635-543270803ec6"}
